<div id="submitting-forms" class="docs-section">
  <h2>Submitting Forms</h2>
  <p>Most Paperboy forms follow a consistent workflow. Here's what to expect when filling out and submitting a form.</p>

  <h3>Finding a Form</h3>
  <p>Browse the sidebar or use the search box to locate the form you need. Click the form name to open it.</p>

  <h3>Filling Out a Form</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Fields marked with an asterisk (<strong>*</strong>) are required.</li>
    <li>Some fields are pre-filled with your employee information (name, email, department, etc.).</li>
    <li>Dropdown fields can be searched by typing &mdash; start typing to filter options.</li>
    <li>Date fields accept manual entry or a date picker.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Multi-Step Forms</h3>
  <p>Longer forms are divided into steps. Use the <strong>Next</strong> and <strong>Previous</strong> buttons to navigate between sections. A progress bar at the top shows your current step.</p>

  <h3>Submitting</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Review your entries, then click <strong>Submit</strong>.</li>
    <li>You'll see a confirmation page upon successful submission.</li>
    <li>If the form requires supervisor approval, your supervisor will be notified automatically.</li>
    <li>You can track the status of your submission from the <strong>Submissions</strong> page.</li>
  </ul>
</div>
